Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; roughly chop whites. Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and halve @button mushrooms{4%oz} (quarter any large mushrooms).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, half the @Old Bay® seasoning{1%unit}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, flipping halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, scallion greens, @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second medium bowl, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{4%tsp}, scallion whites, juice from one lemon wedge, and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste.

In a third medium bowl, whisk together @tempura batter{82%g}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, remaining Old Bay Seasoning, 1/3 cup cold @water{1/3%cup}, and a big pinch of salt. Stir mushrooms into batter until fully coated.

> TIP: If mixture is too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Heat a 1⁄3-inch layer of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, use #tongs{} to add coated mushrooms in a single layer.

> TIP: Work in batches if necessary.

Cook until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on first side and ~{1-2%minutes} on second side. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Season with salt.

While mushrooms cook, cut @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through.

Toast, cut sides up, (place directly on oven rack or use baking sheet) until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Spread cut sides of baguettes with remoulade; fill with mushrooms, @sliced dill pickle{1}, and as much slaw as you like.

Divide sandwiches and fries between plates. Serve with any remaining slaw, any remaining remoulade, and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: If you've got some on hand, serve ketchup or malt vinegar with your fries!